headlines.description: — Kevin Love made five 3-pointers and scored all 23 of his points in the second half, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to their fourth straight win, 105-94 over the Miami Heat on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Love scores 23 in second half, Cavaliers beat Heat 105-94

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry came up just short of Ray Allen's 3-point record Monday night. He still walked away with a win — and a smile.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry falls short of record, but leads Warriors past Pacers

headlines.description: — Chris Boucher matched his season high with 17 points, Yuta Watanabe had 12 points and 10 rebounds for his first career double-double, and the Toronto Raptors used a 70-point first half to rout the Sacramento Kings 124-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors use 70-point first half to rout Kings 124-101

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon scored 32 points, D.J. Augustin added 22 and the Houston Rockets handed the Atlanta Hawks their fifth straight...
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon, Augustin rally Rockets to 132-126 win over Hawks

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 16 of his 42 points in the fourth quarter and the Boston Celtics beat the Milwaukee Bucks 117-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 42, carries Celtics past Bucks 117-103

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 23 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 22 and the Memphis Grizzlies shot better than 50% to dominate the Philadelphia 76ers for a 126-91 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks, Jackson lead Grizzlies in 126-91 blowout of 76ers

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 24 points, 13 rebounds and five blocks, and Dallas hit a season-high 19 3-pointers as the Mavericks routed the Charlotte Hornets 120-96 on Monday night to sweep a back-to-back without All-Star guard Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis leads Luka-less Mavs to 120-96 rout of Hornets

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris had season highs of 24 points and 11 rebounds, leading the Los Angeles Clippers to a 111-95 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Monday night in the teams’ first meeting since the Western Conference finals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Suns 111-95 in rematch of 2021 West finals
